  "text": "In this version of grafana/grafana, legacy alerting engine code (pkg/services/alerting/) has been removed. The three categories requested map to:\n\n**Legacy alert rule storage**: `pkg/services/sqlstore/migrations/alert_mig.go` \u2014 defines the legacy `alert` table schema and migrations (the old dashboard-based alerting). This is the only remaining legacy alerting rule storage code.\n\n**Unified alert rule storage (ngalert)**: The core implementation lives in `pkg/services/ngalert/store/` \u2014 `database.go` defines `DBstore` and `AlertingStore` interface, `alert_rule.go` implements CRUD operations (InsertAlertRules, UpdateAlertRules, DeleteAlertRulesByUID, ListAlertRules, etc.), `models.go` defines the internal `alertRule` xorm model, and `compat.go` handles conversion between DB model and domain model. The domain model `AlertRule` is in `pkg/services/ngalert/models/alert_rule.go`. The `RuleStore` interface is in `pkg/services/ngalert/provisioning/persist.go`.\n\n**Migration scripts (legacy \u2192 unified)**: The `pkg/services/sqlstore/migrations/ualert/` package contains the migration code: `ualert.go` has the `upgradeNgAlerting` migration that moves dashboard alerts to unified alerting and `FixEarlyMigration`; `tables.go` defines the unified alerting table schemas (`alert_rule`, `alert_rule_version`, `alert_instance`, etc.); `migration_service_migration.go` moves legacy alert migration status from migration_log to kvstore; `created_folders_mig.go` migrates folder records created during legacy migration; and `org_upgrade_state_mig.go` tracks per-org migration state between Legacy and UnifiedAlerting types.",
